Dealing the outlier using IQR(Inter-Quartile-Range for TotalCharge columns)

In [27]:
q1= df_t["TotalCharges"].quantile(0.25)
q3 = df_t["TotalCharges"].quantile(0.75)
IQR = q3-q1
print(q1)
print(q3)
print(IQR)

402.225
3786.6
3384.375
In [28]:
lwr_bnd = q1-1.5*IQR
uppr_bnd =q3+1.5*IQR
print(lwr_bnd)
print(uppr_bnd)

-4674.3375
8863.1625
In [29]:
def totl_outlr(x):
    if x>uppr_bnd:
        return uppr_bnd
    elif x<lwr_bnd:
        return lwr_bnd
    else:
        return x
In [30]:
df_t["TotalCharges"]= df_t["TotalCharges"].apply(totl_outlr)

Conclusion:¶

After analyzing the dataset we found that :
  • Monthly contract customers has high probability to churn

-Customer using Internet Service like Fiber Optics, DSL are likely to churn

  • Customer who are non-senior citizen are also likely to churn

  • Among all model ANN and Random Forest seems to good model

Reference:

BLASTCHAR. (n.d.). Telco Customer Churn. Retrieved from www.kaggle.com: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/blastchar/telco-customer-churn/code

Team, S. (2019, July 11). Telco customer churn (11.1.3+). Retrieved from community.ibm.com: https://community.ibm.com/community/user /businessanalytics/blogs/steven-macko/2019/07/11/telco-customer-churn-1113
